Readme for the following tools:
NumuEffTools and NumuDataMcCompTools
M.Ravonel (February 2011)

-----------------------------------------------------

NumuEffTools:
class that allow you to compute efficiency plots, and purity plots
with the output of NumuFlatTree as a function of the cut number or
different varibles.
There is in addition different option of drawing that are optionnal:

The list of function are:

DrawEffPur        // draw eff and pur together : INPUT: sel_cut,sel_true_cut , true_cut
DrawEff           // draw efficiency : INPUT: sel_cut, sel_true_cut , true_cut
DrawPur           // draw purity : INPUT: sel_cut, sel_true_cut , true_cut
DrawCont          // draw contamination : INPUT: sel_cut, sel_true_cut, true_cut
DrawEv            // draw event number for different cut: INPUT: sel_cut
DrawEvRatio       // draw ratio of event number for different mc filesand data : INPUT: sel_cut
DrawFrac          // draw fraction for different cut: INPUT: denom_cut and num_cut
DrawEffvsVar      // plot efficiency vs different variables: INPUT:sel_cut, sel_true_cut , true_cut, variale to plot
DrawPurvsVar      // plot purity vs different variables: INPUT: sel_cut,sel_true_cut , true_cut, variale to plot


DrawEffvsVar2d    // plot efficiency as a function of 2dim variables
                    (X,Y): INPUT: sel_cut, sel_true_cut , true_cut,variable X and variable
                    Y to plot 

DrawPurvsVar2d   // plot purity as a function of 2dim
                    variables (X,Y): INPUT: sel_cut, sel_true_cut , true_cut,variable X
                    and variable Y to plot


//========================================

NumuDataMcCompTools:

Draw Data together with MC file (Neut or Genie or both) for the
variable and the cut you give as input. You will always need to give
the inputs of the histogram you want to plot :
name,title,nbins,xmin,xmax (let's call it hist_about in the
folllowing)

draw_var:        // plot variables for data and mc:
                    INPUT: NumuCut#, variable, additional_cut, hist_about

draw_var_ratio:  // plot ratio for 2 different numu cut number: INPUT:
                    NumuCut#1, NumuCut#2, variable, additional_cut, hist_about

draw_var_DataMc_ratio : //plot ratio between Data and Mc for variable x

+ same function for 2d plots

few additionnal function:
getDataPOT        // get the POT # for a given input file

getMcPOT          // get the MC POT nb from a list of MC files used

makeNorm          // make normalisation